[Auction "S"]
1H pass 4H pass pass pass
[Result ""]
{After SOUTH opens with 1

♥

, NORTH has a small "dilemma".

With 11 points she really is only strong enough to make a jump raise to 3

♥

.

But, with five trumps the hand deserves more. So she just bids 4

♥

instead.

Usually, no matter what your strength, when you have five cards in the Major suit that your partner opens

with you should just jump right to game.}
[BCFlags "1f"]
